The paper deals with the structure and algorithms related to suffix trees, which are primarily used in string processing and data compression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic aspects, which suggest categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also involves information theory and computational complexity, which suggest categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
